{"id":"0804.4852","submitter":"Benjamin  Webb MS","authors":"Benjamin Webb","title":"Dynamics of Functions with an Eventual Negative Schwarzian Derivative","comments":"18 pages, 2 figues, contents have been modified from previous version","journal-ref":null,"doi":null,"report-no":null,"categories":"math.DS","license":"http://arxiv.org/licenses/nonexclusive-distrib/1.0/","abstract":"  In the study of one dimensional dynamical systems one often assumes that the\nfunctions involved have a negative Schwarzian derivative. In this paper we\nconsider a generalization of this condition. Specifically, we consider the\ninterval functions of a real variable having some iterate with a negative\nSchwarzian derivative and show that many known results generalize to this\nlarger class of functions. The introduction of this class was motivated by some\nmaps arising in neuroscience.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 30 Apr 2008 15:55:46 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 14 Jul 2008 20:38:40 GMT"}],"update_date":"2008-07-14"}
